# Lockfile: GitHub Dependency Resolution

`uWebSockets.js` (used by `apps/chat`) is distributed only via GitHub, not npm. In the lockfile, pnpm can resolve `github:` specifiers in two ways:

- **Tarball** (correct): `https://codeload.github.com/.../tar.gz/...` -- plain HTTPS download, no git binary needed
- **Git clone** (breaks Docker): `git+https://github.com/...` with `type: git` -- requires git in the build environment

Our Docker images use slim base images without `git`. If the lockfile uses git-clone resolution, CI builds will fail with `ENOENT: git init`.

## After running `pnpm add` or `pnpm install`

Check the lockfile diff for any `uWebSockets.js` changes. If the resolution has flipped from tarball to git format, restore it:

1. The `importers` entry must use: `version: https://codeload.github.com/uNetworking/uWebSockets.js/tar.gz/{COMMIT}`
2. The `packages` entry must use: `resolution: {tarball: https://codeload.github.com/uNetworking/uWebSockets.js/tar.gz/{COMMIT}}`
3. The `snapshots` entry key must match the tarball URL format

Verify with `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` after any manual edits.
